[build]
dockerfilePath = "backend/Dockerfile"

[deploy]
startCommand = "node server.js"
```

---

## Then Push to GitHub
```
git add .
git commit -m "Add railway config"
git push
```

Railway will **automatically redeploy** as soon as you push!

---

## Why This Happened

Your folder structure is:
```
taskmanager/
├── docker-compose.yml
├── backend/        ← Dockerfile is here
└── frontend/